   "id": "c50763a0-e965-4170-ad0b-5e7f2dca62be",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Flood Risk "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "dd39b369-b7a3-4d83-b18a-61be88ae1c34",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Invert NDVI (so that high value means high flood risk, like the others) "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "be06f85e-0155-4fc4-aac0-04b1d9b4ba65",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "new_data_study_area['inverted_ndvi'] = 1 - new_data_study_area['normalized_mean_ndvi']"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "83b4f52f-e090-4d3c-b63d-2f019412d227",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f5952b82-740c-46f6-93bf-ea65a3c267fc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Flood Risk - Additive Aggregation "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "1834e81f-8b10-4bf1-82a5-6d4f900d13aa",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cols_flood_risk = [\n",
    "    'mean_elev_log_inverted', \n",
    "    'mean_slope_log_inverted', \n",
    "    'normalized_rainfall', \n",
    "    'inverted_ndvi'\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Flood risk (equal weighting) \n",
    "new_data_study_area['flood_risk_add'] = new_data_study_area[cols_flood_risk].mean(axis=1, skipna=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "ec1209cd-7258-42a5-84df-d187078fd4b9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "64df5ca5-ee26-4dee-b65c-733adae933ab",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Flood Risk - Geometric Aggregation "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "b26116b0-f85e-4e1f-a12e-e2d7745e75ba",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cols_flood_risk = [\n",
    "    'mean_elev_log_inverted', \n",
    "    'mean_slope_log_inverted', \n",
    "    'normalized_rainfall', \n",
    "    'inverted_ndvi'\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Replace zeros with a small value to avoid log(0)\n",
    "geo_data = new_data_study_area[cols_flood_risk].replace(0, 1e-6)\n",
    "\n",
    "# same for NaN values\n",
    "geo_data = geo_data.clip(lower=1e-6).fillna(1e-6)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Geometric mean \n",
    "new_data_study_area['flood_risk_geo'] = np.exp(np.log(geo_data).mean(axis=1, skipna=True))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "110ceaba-6fa8-40d4-b9a9-9d8f90f7f3a7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b249e7a8-cc57-44f6-9ee3-e0c668d9f2e8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
